\chapter{Questions}

The polling system only stays stable across recompilations if a question's
identity depends on its content, and on nothing else.  We therefore keep the
question model deliberately small and make each variant able to describe itself
 as ordinary JSON data.  The store hashes that canonical description, so the
same slide source yields the same identifier every time.

