We need a handful of standard-library modules.  Dataclasses give us the frozen
question objects.  JSON plus SHA-256 build the canonical hash.  The word-cloud
aggregator pulls in [[Counter]] for tallying and [[unicodedata]] for
locale-aware punctuation stripping --- both are wanted at module load so the
class definitions can refer to them directly.

