\subsection{Serialisation}

Serialisation omits the fence when it is unset.  That keeps the canonical JSON
for existing open questions byte-for-byte unchanged while still recording the
new rendering hint when authors choose one.

<<open question methods>>=
def to_dict(self) -> dict[str, Any]:
    """Return a JSON-friendly representation of the question."""

    result = {
        "kind": self.kind,
        "text": self.text,
        "max_chars": self.max_chars,
    }
    if self.fence is not None:
        result["fence"] = self.fence
    return result
@

