\subsection{Default stop words}

The default stop-word set focuses on short, structural words that
otherwise dominate a cloud without revealing anything about the topic ---
English copulas, articles, and prepositions, plus their Swedish
counterparts.  We deliberately keep the lists short: pulling the next
hundred entries from an NLP corpus would silently filter content a
lecturer might want to see.  Authors who need a longer list can extend it
per question through [[extra_stop_words]].

<<constants>>=
DEFAULT_STOP_WORDS_EN: frozenset[str] = frozenset({
    "a", "an", "and", "are", "as", "at", "be", "but", "by", "do",
    "for", "from", "had", "has", "have", "he", "her", "his", "i",
    "if", "in", "is", "it", "its", "me", "my", "no", "not", "of",
    "on", "or", "our", "she", "so", "than", "that", "the", "their",
    "them", "they", "this", "to", "too", "was", "we", "were", "what",
    "when", "which", "who", "why", "will", "with", "would", "you",
    "your",
})

DEFAULT_STOP_WORDS_SV: frozenset[str] = frozenset({
    "att", "av", "de", "den", "det", "du", "ej", "eller", "en", "ett",
    "för", "från", "har", "i", "in", "inte", "jag", "med", "men",
    "mig", "min", "mitt", "och", "om", "på", "så", "ska", "som",
    "till", "var", "vi", "vid", "är", "över",
})

DEFAULT_STOP_WORDS: frozenset[str] = (
    DEFAULT_STOP_WORDS_EN | DEFAULT_STOP_WORDS_SV
)
