Multiple-choice options are stored as JSON arrays, but the frozen dataclass uses
a tuple so callers cannot mutate a registered question after hashing it.

<<rebuild stored multiple-choice question>>=
if kind == "mc":
    return MCQuestion(
        text=str(data["text"]),
        options=tuple(data["options"]),
        multi=bool(data.get("multi", False)),
    )
@

Stored JSON is less typed than the in-memory dataclasses.  We therefore coerce
[[fence]] back to [[str]] when it is present so older or hand-edited store files
still rebuild into the same [[OpenQuestion]] shape as freshly rendered
questions.

<<rebuild stored open question>>=
if kind == "open":
    return OpenQuestion(
        text=str(data["text"]),
        max_chars=int(data.get("max_chars", 280)),
        fence=None if data.get("fence") is None else str(data["fence"]),
    )
@

Scale reconstruction keeps default bounds and labels here rather than in the
store so old records inherit the same defaults as newly authored questions.

<<rebuild stored scale question>>=
if kind == "scale":
    return ScaleQuestion(
        text=str(data["text"]),
        low=int(data.get("low", 1)),
        high=int(data.get("high", 5)),
        low_label=str(data.get("low_label", "")),
        high_label=str(data.get("high_label", "")),
